dct_description_sm: Relief shown pictorially. "Cum privilegio." Insets: Northampton -- Peterborow. Includes "The armes of all those honorable families that have bene created Earles of Northa[m]pto[n], since ye Normans conquest." Text on verso with caption title: Northampton-shire. Book I. Chap. 28; p. 55-56; signature N2. From: The theatre of the empire of Great Britaine ... / divided and described by Iohn Speed. London : And are to be solde by I. Sudbury and G. Humble, 1611.
dct_publisher_sm: [London] : are to be sold by George Humbell in ye Popes head alley, 1610.
